1038
01:06:55,242 --> 01:06:57,710
[ duck quacking ]

1039
01:07:19,433 --> 01:07:24,237
I, Ward Allen, was wrong.

1040
01:07:30,144 --> 01:07:35,114
I, Ward Allen,
may have been wrong.

1041
01:07:35,116 --> 01:07:37,150
Before you check to see

1042
01:07:37,152 --> 01:07:39,485
if the fires of hell
have turned to ice,

1043
01:07:39,487 --> 01:07:42,955
let me emphasize
that I would do

1044
01:07:42,957 --> 01:07:44,157
or have done

1045
01:07:44,159 --> 01:07:47,593
nothing different
in my life.

1046
01:07:47,595 --> 01:07:50,296
But it seems
that perhaps our world

1047
01:07:50,298 --> 01:07:52,498
met a fork in the road,

1048
01:07:52,500 --> 01:07:55,868
and the world took one path,

1049
01:07:55,870 --> 01:07:58,104
and I took the other.

1050
01:08:00,574 --> 01:08:02,675
Perhaps this is
an inevitable result,

1051
01:08:02,677 --> 01:08:05,545
and each of us
are doomed to find ourselves

1052
01:08:05,547 --> 01:08:07,447
on a path alone
in the end,

1053
01:08:07,449 --> 01:08:11,651
especially those of us
who found the world as it was

1054
01:08:11,653 --> 01:08:13,986
to be a close
to perfect place...

1055
01:08:13,988 --> 01:08:17,256
those who accepted
that the affairs of men

1056
01:08:17,258 --> 01:08:18,791
are like those of a river,

1057
01:08:18,793 --> 01:08:22,895
where time and tide are
the ultimate shapers of a life,

1058
01:08:22,897 --> 01:08:26,432
where procreation,
migration, and even death

1059
01:08:26,434 --> 01:08:28,367
are spokes
of the same wheel

1060
01:08:28,369 --> 01:08:33,606
that turns in heaven's vault
just the way it should.

1061
01:08:33,608 --> 01:08:35,908
But there are others
who are determined

1062
01:08:35,910 --> 01:08:39,479
to reshape that wheel
and turn back the tide,

1063
01:08:39,481 --> 01:08:42,315
and they appear
ready to do it.

1064
01:08:42,317 --> 01:08:45,852
Maybe they are right,
representing as they do,

1065
01:08:45,854 --> 01:08:47,887
an impulse
in the breast of man

1066
01:08:47,889 --> 01:08:51,791
that drives our species
toward restless industry.

1067
01:08:51,793 --> 01:08:54,427
Maybe we are here
to remake everything,

1068
01:08:54,429 --> 01:08:56,562
reshape everything,

1069
01:08:56,564 --> 01:08:59,332
create our own new idea
of perfection

1070
01:08:59,334 --> 01:09:03,402
and leave God's idea
to the dim shades of history.

1071
01:09:05,038 --> 01:09:09,375
And maybe I, having fought
against that new idea,

1072
01:09:09,377 --> 01:09:11,511
rejected that idea,

1073
01:09:11,513 --> 01:09:14,180
found that idea abhorrent,

1074
01:09:14,182 --> 01:09:16,315
maybe I was wrong.

1075
01:09:16,317 --> 01:09:18,484
But I do not think so.

1076
01:09:18,486 --> 01:09:22,688
Because I believe
if we have grown as a species,

1077
01:09:22,690 --> 01:09:26,125
it has been because
of the test of wildness,

1078
01:09:26,127 --> 01:09:30,196
and if we succeed in remaking
wildness into mildness,

1079
01:09:30,198 --> 01:09:33,132
then we will begin
to diminish.

1080
01:09:35,702 --> 01:09:37,603
But all I have
accomplished

1081
01:09:37,605 --> 01:09:40,006
is a broken knuckle
or two

1082
01:09:40,008 --> 01:09:42,141
and hurting myself
and my own

1083
01:09:42,143 --> 01:09:46,412
more than those who are
the target of my calumny.

1084
01:09:46,414 --> 01:09:49,048
So perhaps I'd do better

1085
01:09:49,050 --> 01:09:51,017
to take my pokes
on these pages

1086
01:09:51,019 --> 01:09:53,286
and take direction
from the Bard...

1087
01:09:53,288 --> 01:09:57,023
"Let there be gall
enough in thy ink."

1088
01:09:57,858 --> 01:09:59,725
It's worth a try.

1089
01:10:09,303 --> 01:10:14,640
Did you read my article?

1090
